sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser Client
    participant API as API / CLI Client
    participant Envoy as Envoy Proxy
    participant Proxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP
    participant IdP as OIDC / OpenShift<br/>OAuth Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OSUser as OpenShift User API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Upstream as Upstream Service
    participant Redis as Redis (optional)<br/>6379/TCP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: Browser-Based OIDC/OAuth Authentication
        Browser->>Proxy: GET /oauth2/start<br/>HTTP(S), No Auth
        Proxy->>Proxy: Generate CSRF token<br/>Set CSRF cookie
        Proxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to IdP authorize endpoint
        Browser->>IdP: GET /authorize<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>client_id, state, nonce
        IdP->>Browser: Login form
        Browser->>IdP: POST credentials
        IdP->>Browser: 302 Redirect to /oauth2/callback<br/>authorization code
        Browser->>Proxy: GET /oauth2/callback?code=...&state=...<br/>CSRF cookie
        Proxy->>IdP: POST /token<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>client credentials + auth code
        IdP-->>Proxy: Access token + ID token + Refresh token
        Proxy->>Redis: Store session (if Redis enabled)
        Proxy-->>Browser: 302 Redirect to original URL<br/>Set session cookie
        Browser->>Proxy: GET /* (any path)<br/>Session cookie
        Proxy->>Proxy: Validate session cookie
        Proxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>GAP-Auth + X-Forwarded-User<br/>X-Forwarded-Email + X-Forwarded-Groups
        Upstream-->>Proxy: Response
        Proxy-->>Browser: Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over API,Upstream: Flow 2: Bearer Token Authentication (CLI/API)
        API->>Proxy: GET /* or /oauth2/auth<br/>Authorization: Bearer <token>
        alt K8s Service Account Token
            Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST TokenReview<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>SA token
            K8sAPI-->>Proxy: TokenReview result<br/>(authenticated, username, groups)
        else OpenShift sha256~ Token
            Proxy->>OSUser: GET /apis/user.openshift.io/v1/users/~<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer token
            OSUser-->>Proxy: User info (username, email, groups)
        else OIDC JWT Token
            Proxy->>Proxy: Verify JWT locally<br/>via JWKS (cached)
        end
        Proxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>GAP-Auth + X-Forwarded-* headers
        Upstream-->>Proxy: Response
        Proxy-->>API: Response
    end

    rect rgb(245, 255, 230)
        Note over Envoy,Proxy: Flow 3: Envoy ext_authz Integration
        Envoy->>Proxy: GET /oauth2/auth<br/>HTTP (pod-local, plaintext)<br/>Forwarded headers + cookies
        Proxy->>Proxy: Validate session / token<br/>(same chain as Flow 1 or 2)
        alt Authenticated
            Proxy-->>Envoy: 200 OK<br/>X-Forwarded-User, X-Forwarded-Email<br/>X-Forwarded-Groups headers
        else Unauthenticated
            Proxy-->>Envoy: 401 Unauthorized
        else Invalid/Forbidden
            Proxy-->>Envoy: 403 Forbidden
        end
    end
